description.narrative: DNDi is committed to developing safe, effective, and affordable treatments for people with neglected tropical diseases and for neglected patients. Since 2003, DNDi has worked with its worldwide network of partners to: 1. Develop 2 new chemical entities: fexinidazole, the first all-oral treatment for sleeping sickness; and ravidasvir, a simple-to-use and affordable treatment for hepatitis C. 2. Develop 7 new treatments from existing molecules and recombining drugs to bring better treatments to patients for malaria, Chagas disease, leishmaniasis, and paediatric HIV. 3. Initiate GARDP, a not-for-profit research and development organization developing and delivering new or improved antibiotic treatments.
DNDi’s objective is to deliver 25 new treatments for neglected patients by 2028.
